<!--  TAB 0 — DIZZINESS                          -->

<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

<div class="tab-panel active" id="panel-0">

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Classifications of Dizziness</div>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th class="th-diz">Type</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Patient's Description</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Cause</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Key Feature</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Vertigo</strong></td><td>"Room is spinning"</td><td>Vestibular system</td><td>Peripheral (inner ear) or Central (brainstem/cerebellum)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Presyncope</strong></td><td>"About to faint"</td><td>Cardiovascular</td><td>No illusion of motion; drop in BP/perfusion</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Disequilibrium</strong></td><td>"Falling / leaning"</td><td>Locomotor / proprioception</td><td>Drunk-like gait; no head sensation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Non-specific</strong></td><td>"Lightheaded / foggy"</td><td>Psychiatric / idiopathic</td><td>No anatomic localizer; anxiety, depression, meds</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Central vs Peripheral Vertigo ⭐⭐⭐</div>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th class="th-diz">Feature</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Central (BAD — ADMIT)</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Peripheral (GOOD — send home)</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Nystagmus direction</strong></td><td>Vertical, direction-changing, multidirectional</td><td>Horizontal–torsional, UNIDIRECTIONAL</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Nystagmus fatiguability</strong></td><td>NON-fatigable (unrelenting)</td><td>FATIGABLE (stops with fixation/time)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Head Impulse (HI)</strong></td><td>NORMAL (no catch-up saccades)</td><td>ABNORMAL (catch-up saccades present)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Skew deviation</strong></td><td><em class="hl">PRESENT</em> — 100% central</td><td>Absent</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Onset</strong></td><td>Continuous, minutes–hours</td><td>Positional, &lt;1 min unless re-provoked</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Neurologic deficits</strong></td><td>Often present (diplopia, dysarthria, ataxia)</td><td>ABSENT</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Pattern</strong></td><td>NOT positional</td><td>Positional vertigo (BPPV)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Classic example</strong></td><td>Stroke / TIA</td><td>Vestibular neuritis</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="hbox hbox-danger">
      <strong>🚨 Central Red Flags: Double vision + dizziness, Thunderclap headache, Horner's syndrome, Skew deviation, Direction-changing nystagmus, Vertical nystagmus</strong>
    </div>
    <div class="hbox hbox-ok">
      <strong>✅ Peripheral = Safe to manage outpatient if no vomiting/dehydration:</strong>
      BPPV · Vestibular Neuritis · Orthostatic Hypotension · Migraine
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">HINTS Examination ⭐⭐⭐</div>
    <div class="hbox hbox-diz"><strong>Sensitivity 99.2%, Specificity 97%</strong> for stroke within first 48 hrs. Perform on ANY patient with dizziness not clearly peripheral.</div>
    <div class="hints-grid">
      <div class="hints-card">
        <div class="letter">H</div>
        <div class="hname">Head Impulse</div>
        <div class="hdesc">Hold head, fix on examiner's nose, rapidly turn head side-to-side. Watch for CATCH-UP SACCADES.</div>
        <div class="hresult">
          <span class="tag tag-g">ABNORMAL = peripheral</span><br>
          <span class="tag tag-r">NORMAL = central 🚨</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hints-card">
        <div class="letter">N</div>
        <div class="hname">Nystagmus</div>
        <div class="hdesc">Observe in primary, left, right, up, down gaze.</div>
        <div class="hresult">
          <span class="tag tag-g">Horizontal unidirectional = peripheral</span><br>
          <span class="tag tag-r">Vertical / direction-changing = central 🚨</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hints-card">
        <div class="letter">TS</div>
        <div class="hname">Test of Skew</div>
        <div class="hdesc">Cover/uncover alternate eyes. Watch for sudden VERTICAL movement of uncovered eye.</div>
        <div class="hresult">
          <span class="tag tag-g">Absent = peripheral</span><br>
          <span class="tag tag-r">PRESENT vertical skew = central 🚨 (100%!)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hbox hbox-info"><strong>HINTS interpretation:</strong> HI=normal + N=vertical + TS=present skew → <em class="hl">CENTRAL — Rush to ER!</em></div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Dix-Hallpike Maneuver (for BPPV) ⭐⭐⭐</div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="badge badge-diz">Procedure</div>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li>Seat patient upright</li>
          <li>Turn head <strong>45°</strong> toward tested side</li>
          <li>Rapidly lay patient back, neck extended, head hangs over edge</li>
          <li>Hold 30 seconds — observe for nystagmus</li>
          <li>Repeat on contralateral side</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted)">Pre-check: No cervical instability, no vertebral artery insufficiency</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="badge badge-ok">Positive Test = BPPV</div>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li class="star">Latency of <strong>5–40 seconds</strong></li>
          <li class="star">Torsional + <strong>upbeating</strong> nystagmus</li>
          <li class="star">FATIGABLE (diminishes with repeated provocation)</li>
          <li class="star">Reproducible with position change</li>
          <li>Nystagmus <strong>changes direction</strong> when patient sits up again</li>
          <li class="ok">If positive → EPLEY maneuver</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Vertigo Duration → Diagnosis ⭐⭐⭐</div>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th class="th-diz">Duration</th><th class="th-diz">Etiology</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><em class="hl">Seconds (5–40s latency)</em></td><td>BPPV · Vasovagal reaction</td></tr>
          <tr><td><em class="hl">Minutes</em></td><td>VBI (Vertebrobasilar Insufficiency) · TIA · Hypoglycemia</td></tr>
          <tr><td><em class="hl">Hours (up to 7 hrs)</em></td><td>Ménière's Disease</td></tr>
          <tr><td><em class="hl">Days</em></td><td>Vestibular Neuritis · Vertiginous Migraine · Brainstem/Cerebellar Stroke</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Common Otologic Etiologies</div>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th class="th-diz">Condition</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Key Features</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Duration</th>
          <th class="th-diz">Differentiating Feature</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>BPPV</strong> ⭐ Most Common</td><td>Brief, positional, no hearing loss</td><td>Seconds</td><td>Triggered by head movement, Dix-Hallpike (+)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Vestibular Neuritis</strong></td><td>Constant vertigo, post-viral, ± hearing loss</td><td>Days</td><td>Acute onset, abnormal head impulse, peripheral HINTS</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Ménière's Disease</strong></td><td>Episodic vertigo, chronic</td><td>Hours (≤7)</td><td><em class="hl">Fluctuating hearing loss + tinnitus + ear fullness</em></td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Vestibular Migraine</strong></td><td>Vertigo without severe headache</td><td>Minutes–hours</td><td>History of migraine, episodic</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title" style="color:var(--diz)">Imaging & Labs</div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="badge badge-ok">MRI ✅ Best</div>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li>Best for posterior circulation (brainstem/cerebellum)</li>
          <li>Acute DWI: 80% detection rate (20% false negative)</li>
          <li>53% false negative for small strokes at 6–48hrs</li>
          <li>Preferred during brain attacks (1st hour)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="badge badge-warn">CT Scan ⚠️ Limited</div>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li>Only 16% sensitive for stroke</li>
