        <h4>Secondary HA (MORE DANGEROUS — rule out FIRST)</h4>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li>WITH identifiable underlying cause</li>
          <li>Brain tumor (progressive, worse AM, papilledema)</li>
          <li>Traumatic Brain Injury</li>
          <li>Giant Cell Arteritis (age &gt;50, ESR &gt;50, jaw claudication)</li>
          <li>Meningitis (fever, neck stiffness)</li>
          <li class="danger">Subarachnoid Hemorrhage — MUST RULE OUT first in thunderclap HA</li>
          <li>Cerebral venous sinus thrombosis (female + OCP) ⭐</li>
          <li>Ruptured aneurysm ⭐</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-b">
        <h4>Primary HA (NO identifiable cause)</h4>
        <ul class="kf">
          <li>Migraine</li>
          <li>Tension-type headache (TTH) — Most Common</li>
          <li>Cluster headache</li>
          <li>Hemicrania continua</li>
          <li>Primary thunderclap HA (only after excluding SAH!)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sub-title">SNOOP10 Red Flags for Secondary HA ⭐⭐</div>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th class="th-head">Flag</th><th class="th-head">What to look for</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>S</strong>ystemic</td><td>Fever, chills, weight loss, malignancy, HIV, immunosuppression, jaw claudication (GCA)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>N</strong>eurologic</td><td>Focal/global neuro deficits, diplopia, motor weakness, ataxia, pulsatile tinnitus</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>O</strong>nset (sudden)</td><td>Thunderclap — reaches peak &lt;1 minute → rule out SAH</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>O</strong>nset (age)</td><td>New-onset HA &gt;50 years OR &lt;5 years</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>attern change</td><td>Progressive HA, change in character, evolution to daily HA</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>ostural</td><td>Worse lying down (↑ICP) or standing (↓ICP — CSF leak)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>recipitated by Valsalva</td><td>Cough, exertion, sex-induced HA</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>apilledema</td><td>On fundoscopy — always order imaging</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>regnancy</td><td>New or changed HA during/after pregnancy</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>P</strong>ainkiller overuse</td><td>MOH — NSAIDs/Triptans/Opioids too frequently</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

