        <div class="badge badge-head">CGRP — Key Peptide</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px">Released during migraine attack → inflammation + vasodilation of cerebral/meningeal vessels. Normalizes with Triptan therapy. Led to development of <strong>CGRP antagonists</strong> (Rimegepant, Atogepant) and <strong>CGRP mAbs</strong> (Erenumab, Fremanezumab, Galcanezumab).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
