    <div class="flow-col">
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--ok);background:var(--ok-light)">PERIPHERAL<br>(Abnormal HI, horizontal nystagmus, no skew, fatigable)<br>Duration + triggers → BPPV / Neuritis / Ménière's</div>
      <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--ok)">SEND HOME<br>Epley / Meclizine / Hydrate / Anti-vertigo max 3 days</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-col">
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--danger);background:var(--danger-light)">CENTRAL<br>(Normal HI, vertical/direction-changing nystagmus, skew present, diplopia, dysarthria)</div>
      <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--danger)">ADMIT + MRI + Stroke workup</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sub-title" style="margin-top:24px">Approach to Headache</div>
<div class="flow" style="font-size:12px">
  <div class="flow-box" style="background:#2c2825;color:#fff">New Headache</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box"><strong>SNOOP10 screening</strong> — Any red flags?</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-row">
    <div class="flow-col">
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--danger);background:var(--danger-light)">YES → Suspect SECONDARY<br>Thunderclap? → CT → LP (SAH)<br>Progressive? → MRI (tumor)<br>Fever + neck stiffness? → LP (meningitis)<br>Female + OCP? → MRV (CVST)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-col">
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--ok);background:var(--ok-light)">NO → Likely PRIMARY<br>Characterize by PUMA, duration, associated Sx<br>Migraine / Tension / Cluster / Other</div>
      <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
      <div class="flow-box" style="border-color:var(--ok)">Migraine → Triptans (acute) + Prophylaxis<br>Tension → NSAIDs; NO triptans<br>Cluster → O₂ first-line; SC Sumatriptan</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sub-title" style="margin-top:24px">Approach to Cognitive Complaints</div>
<div class="flow" style="font-size:12px">
  <div class="flow-box" style="background:#2c2825;color:#fff">Cognitive Complaint</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">Collateral history (timing, progression, domains affected, meds, PMHx)</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">MMSE + MoCA (if MMSE normal but still suspected) → Labs → MRI (mandatory)</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box"><strong>FIRST: Rule out REVERSIBLE causes</strong> (thyroid, B12, glucose, electrolytes, infection, medications)</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">If irreversible: Amyloid PET / CSF biomarkers (Aβ42, p-tau, t-tau) for specific diagnosis</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">Treat: Symptomatic + Lifestyle + Family support</div>
</div>

<div class="sub-title" style="margin-top:24px">Approach to Seizures</div>
<div class="flow" style="font-size:12px">
  <div class="flow-box" style="background:#2c2825;color:#fff">Suspected Seizure Event</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">Is this truly a seizure? (Rule out mimics: syncope, hypoglycemia, TIA, panic, PNES)</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">Characterize: Focal vs Generalized vs Unknown onset<br>Semiology, duration, postictal state, triggers</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">EEG (standard → sleep EEG → video-EEG) + MRI brain</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">Metabolic workup: Na, K, Ca, Mg, glucose, LFTs, renal function<br>Most common metabolic cause: HYPO/HYPERNATREMIA</div>
  <div class="flow-arr">↓</div>
  <div class="flow-box">AED based on seizure type + patient factors (age, sex, other meds)<br>Goal: Seizure-free with fewest side effects</div>
</div>
